            "answer_text": "Not without really, really stretching the definition. Ketchup is cooked, unlike most smoothies. And ketchup has substantial amounts of vinegar, not generally a smoothie ingredient, and sugar, which is usually very limited in fruit smoothies. All of that leads to a very strongly flavored product which is consumed in condiment quantities, not beverage quantities. As the joke goes: Knowledge is knowing that a tomato is a fruit. Wisdom is not putting it in a fruit salad. ",
